<item>
            <title>[LU-16313] PCC: change PCC type with bit matching for attach</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16313</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We only support two PCC type: readonly and readwirte:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;enum&lt;/span&gt; lu_pcc_type {
    LU_PCC_NONE = 0,
    LU_PCC_READWRITE,
    LU_PCC_READONLY,
    LU_PCC_MAX
};
struct lu_pcc_attach {
    __u32 pcca_type; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* PCC type */&lt;/span&gt;
    __u32 pcca_id; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* archive ID &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; readwrite, group ID &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; readonly */&lt;/span&gt;
};&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The attach&#160; data structure @lu_pcc_attach is using 32 bit @pcca_type to determine the type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we could change it from &quot;== LU_PCC_READWRITE&quot; to &quot;&amp;amp;LU_PCC_READWRITE&quot; to determine the PCC type via 2 bit matching. The left bits can be used as other flags for PCC attach such the asynchronous attach via the command &quot;lfs pcc attach -A&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
